cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection using CNNs, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of a regressor to iteratively move and scale elements of the grid suggests a machine learning approach (cs.LG, cs.AI). The reduction in the number of boxes to be processed could also be seen as a computational efficiency improvement, which could fall under robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of CNNs and iterative techniques suggests a neural network approach, which could also fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
